    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for esc.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 8.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "The esc packages contain the Enterprise Security Client (ESC), which allows\nthe user to manage security smart cards. The primary function of the tool\nis to enroll smart cards, so that they can be used for common cryptographic\noperations, such as to secure e-mail and website access.\n\nBug Fix(es) and Enhancement(s):\n\n* Create explicit pcsc-lite requirement to assure recent pcsc-lite fix\n(BZ#1972570)\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
